<TEXT>
the promotion of voting is not among the 
priorities of many of americas companies even though the nation is 
facing a voter participation crisis a private group says 
people for the american way said thursday that 60 percent of the 
fortune 500 companies surveyed conduct little or no organized 
nonpartisan voter registration education or getoutthevote 
activities 
and only 6 percent have voter participation activities that 
reach beyond their own employees the group said 
ninetyone of the fortune 500s top 100 corporations responded 
to the groups phone and mail surveys which were conducted in 
april and may 
melanne verveer vice president of the group said the nation is 
facing the grim possibility that for the first time in its 
history less than half of the eligible voters will be going to the 
polls in the presidential election 
this crisis in participation is the result of a 
threedecadelong slide in voter participation that threatens to 
turn our government by all the people into government by less than 
half the people ms verveer said 
she said new institutions must take the lead to stem declining 
voter participation and she noted that a few businesses have taken 
exciting initiatives 
sherrod brown ohio secretary of state said many major 
corporations in ohio have printed up voter registration forms and 
mailed them to customers as part of their monthly billing 
procedures 
we figure we will put literally millions of registration 
forms without government spending into prospective voters 
hands brown said 
bruce akers vice president of the clevelandbased ameritrust 
bank said his company began offering voter registration services 
in cuyahoga county to its customers and the general public in 1982 
as a result of our success and the fact that weve had such a 
good response were going to take this program to the 11 other 
counties in ohio where we have branches akers said 
nevertheless verveer said that the inescapable conclusion of 
our study is that for the majority of corporations voter 
registration is nowhere to be found on their list of priorities 
the washingtonbased people for the american way is a 
nonpartisan constitutional liberties organization that conducts 
public education programs on constitutional issues 
</TEXT>
