would deliver a comprehensive report to the council on the 
ceasefire declaration troop withdrawal prisoner exchange and 
other elements of a un peace plan 
iran and iraq have waged war since 1980 when iraq invaded 
iranian territory the death toll is estimated at 1 million 
the security council in july 1987 adopted a resolution calling 
for a ceasefire in the war which has prompted an escalated us 
naval presence in the gulf 
iraq accepted the proposal but it was not until last month that 
iran after a series of battlefield defeats said it too would 
accept the resolution since then iraq has launched several 
attacks on iran to bolster its bargaining position 
iranian foreign minister ali akbar velayati met the un chief 
for more than one hour thursday the iranian envoy made no comments 
as he left the meeting 
iraq says it needs the direct talks as a guarantee of sincerity 
from iran which it fears will seek only a temporary truce to 
regroup forces 
