efficiency of nonfarm businesses in producing goods and services 
declined 17 percent in the quarter ended june 30 its first 
decline in two years and the biggest drop since 1981 
productivity had risen at an annual rate of 34 percent in the 
second quarter and had been improving at a rate of 1 percent to 2 
percent annually in the previous three years 
reflecting the strong economic expansion output of goods and 
services by those businesses responsible for threefourths of us 
economic activity rose 47 percent in the second quarter 
